Bug 742137 - Run ISPDB on Django 1.4

List of changes:
- Moved static files (css, .js, images, etc.) to config/static (NEW DJANGO LAYOUT)
- Moved manage.py to one top-level dir (NEW DJANGO LAYOUT)
- Removed local_settings. Using settings.py for development now.
- Changes in settings.py to work with Django 1.4
- Changed templates to use STATIC_URL instead of MEDIA_URL
- Changes apache/production.py, apache/ispdb.wsgi and apache/wsgi.conf to use recommended WSGI functions of Django 1.4
- Added csrf_token to post forms
- Changes in urls.py to use new staticserve methods
add README for github

Merge pull request #5 from sergiocharpineljr/master

Add support for editions, deletions and report issues.
fix typo
fix pluralize problem
show_issue: add another link to the configuration page on the bottom of the page
add timezone support (and removed unnecessary fixture data)
str-fy string on __str__ method (since they're always unicode)
add incoming_username_form to add configuration form. bug #518510
remove confirmations attribute from Config class. It is not being used.
improve report page display
remove delete confirmations and add an UNDO button which will be available for 24hrs. remove TZ support (we are not using it)
add tests for issue feature
fix edit and repot links in details page
finish error display and merge in show_issue page. And added edit suggested configuration support
minor changes/fix in show_issue page
add initial support for issues feature.
fix edit title
fix bug when adding a deleted domain on edit form
add domain name to search field in admin page
fix error display in details template during approve and delete actions
fix asking domain name check and empty forms problem
add tests for delete domain feature
fix delete permission
enable config in admin site so we can purge them from there
delete configuration: add initial support
list/xml should list only approved configs.
remove votes and status from Domain. Add status to Config to hold approved, invalid, requested and deleted states
remove UnclaimedDomain and using DomainRequest instead
add edit tests
add xml1.0 test. code clean up
fix tests to work with login_required and DomainRequest
fix xml export for DomainRequest
remove unused file
check_domain view is not necessary because adding a new domain will create a DomainRequest object and its name is not unique
fix convert.py to add config as approved
add more tests to test_add
check for duplicated domain names in form
fix domain name check
small cleanups
fix test_add
check max number of forms. add formset clean in edit view
fix internationalized domain names problem
add __init__.py file so we can run specific nose tests

add initial support for domain editions. Important changes:
- Domain class now represents a approved domain
- DomainRequest represents a requested domain and are not unique
- non admin users should be able to modify their requested domain (while it is not accepted)
Update jQuery because I need .on function
add view: if formset has errors, show form. And added edit var, to show the form when editing domains
Fix bug when form was not validated, the page was reloaded and then the user added another domain. It would update TOTAL_FORMS to 2, even if we have more than 2 Email domains
Validating domain names and discarding empty ones
